## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: thing|rate_effect — Identity is the error produced when motion is sampled too slowly. Fast recurrence mistaken for permanence.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: owned|passing_through — The selfplex is private but not owned, portable but not persistent. Felt as "I" because the knot is currently tight here.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: substance|repetition — A knot is repetition, not substance. It stabilizes action, not truth.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: tightening|loosening — Knots tighten and loosen. If a pattern cannot loosen without panic, it is no longer useful.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: recurrence|reweaving — The Threadplex continuously reweaves. Fibres change, context shifts, continuity inferred after the fact.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: boundary|tension — The selfplex has no boundary, no memory store, no executive function. It is tension, not container.

## Z-State
:threadplex_flow — The only actual process: continuous reweaving from which all identity effects emerge as rate artifacts.

